HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 308
BY REPRESENTATIVE MILLER
COMMENDATIONS: Commends His Holiness Pope Leo XIV for his faithful leadership
of the Catholic Church
1 A RESOLUTION
2 To commend His Holiness Pope Leo XIV for his faithful leadership of the Catholic Church.
3 WHEREAS, His Holiness Pope Leo XIV has accepted the sacred responsibility of
4 leading the Catholic Church with wisdom, humility, courage, and unwavering devotion to
5 God and humanity; and
6 WHEREAS, the Holy Father's commitment to peace, mercy, justice, compassion, and
7 the dignity of every human person serves as a guiding light to nations and peoples across the
8 globe; and
9 WHEREAS, the state of Louisiana possesses a rich and enduring Catholic heritage
10 deeply rooted in the faith traditions brought by French and Spanish settlers, and these
11 traditions continue to shape the spiritual, cultural, and historic identity of our communities;
12 and
13 WHEREAS, from the historic parishes of South Louisiana to the sacred bells of
14 St. Louis Cathedral in New Orleans, the Catholic faith has long inspired the people of
15 Louisiana toward charity, perseverance, service, hospitality, and devotion to God; and
16 WHEREAS, the citizens of Louisiana recognize and honor the Holy Father's
17 dedication to the poor, the vulnerable, the suffering, and those seeking hope, reconciliation,
18 and spiritual renewal in times of uncertainty; and
19 WHEREAS, Louisianians stand united in prayer and goodwill with Catholics and
20 people of faith around the world in celebration of the pontificate of Pope Leo XIV and in
21 support of his sacred ministry; and
